args: All the stamina in the world won't change\nanything if I just hunt monsters at random.
I must return to the Halidom and challenge\nthat gold-crown Rathalos anew.
Tch! I'm finished if it finds me here.\nI must see my way through this.
(It landed! Might it be searching for me?)
(Well, if the beast truly seeks me out,\nI'll gain little by trying to hide.)
(The only choice is to challenge it\nto single combat here and now!\nGo, Berserker! Slay your foe!)

(...And yet, why do I hesitate?
This is my chance for a rematch
where either the glory of victory
or a warrior's death await!)
(...No. It must not be this way.)
(If I wager my life on this fight,\nit will doubtless end in the same\nhumiliation as last time.)
(I've no wish to be toyed with and\nslaughtered like a mouse before a cat!)
(I must stay hidden. I must stay calm.)
(I want to hunt that monster,\nand I want to DEFEAT it!)
(I'll crawl on the ground like a worm if it\ngives me that chance! I'll suffer any\nindignity for just one clear shot!)
(I don't give a damn what it takesâ€”\nI WILL get through this!)
(My weapon may be blunted,\nbut a hunter always has this...)
Ho, Rathalos! Come for me, if you dare!
This scorched smell...\nI thought I was dead for sure.
It seems Rathalos spied the fiend from\nearlier and burned it to a crisp.
Avoiding conflict with a decoy is not\na route I am much familiar with.
Still, this sort of maneuver isn't so bad. \nA true hunter's move, in fact!
After all, one cannot live only on fights\nwhere their life is tossed aside!
